WorldStage Newsonline– First Bank of Nigeria Limited said that its customers using Verve Cards had begun to enjoy extra five (5) litres of fuel for every N3,000 fuel purchased using the card at specified periods. Mrs Folake Ani-Mumuney, Group Head, Marketing & Corporate Communications of the bank  in a statement on Tuesday in Lagos said that the customers were enjoying the benefit under its Free Fuel promotion which kicked-off on July 6. According to her, the Free Fuel promo is activated by FirstBank in collaboration with Verve International and Oando Plc. “In the promo, for a minimum of N3,000 fuel purchase, FirstBank Verve Cardholders will receive 5 extra litres of fuel for FREE instantly at selected Oando Fuel Stations across Lagos every Monday, Tuesday and Thursday. “The Oando fuel stations where the promo will run are Abijo (Lekki Stillwaters), Fola-Agoro, Maryland, Agege-Bypass, Lakowe, Lawanson, Ojodu- Berger, Alapere, Shiro Road (Fadeyi Ikorodu Rd.), Awolowo Rd (by Fire Service), Marina, and Tradefair stations,” she said. She said that the promotion, which ends on July  24, was between the hours of 6am and 6pm. “Verve card is a secure debit card that allows the cardholder to conveniently meet day to day financial needs such as payment for goods and services, airtime recharge, bill payments, funds transfer and more. “It is accepted across all ATMs, POS, Web and Mobile Platforms in Nigeria. Pick up your FirstBank Verve card today at any of our branches and start getting rewarded,” she said.